Neurologic syndromes in craniovertebral dysplasias. Sixty-two craniovertebral dysplasy patients could be divided into three groups with respect to neurologic syndromes displaying disorders at different levels in a neurologic and X-rays investigation. The authors stress the diagnostic importance of a purposeful X-ray investigation of craniovertebral area in cases of neurologic symptoms and external signs of dysplasy, and the value of timely diagnosis for prevention of neurologic complications.